Vitamin C is a great ingredient to brighten the skin, but I’ve personally been skeptical of trying it cause there are so many variants & not to forget I have sensitive skin
Recently I tried @sadhev’s ayurvedic vitamin C & I love how it was gentle on my skin
It’s fragrance free which I really appreciate & has ingredients like amla, pomegranate seed oil & kakadu plum that has 100 times more Vitamin C
Also infused with hyaluronic acid that helps hydrate the skin 
Do try it out!

I celebrated my bday recently & I was just reminded of how blessed I am & I am truly grateful for it 🩷
You guys have stuck around with me, so I really wanted to do something special for you 🤗

I wanted to giveaway 3 @charlottetilbury products to one of you 
✨Hollywood flawless filter 
✨Glowgasm beauty light wand 
✨Luxury eyeshadow palette 

& you don’t have to do anything crazy to get it, just
✨Follow me 🫶 if you haven’t already 
✨💖Like & share this reel

@charlottetilbury is exclusively available on @mynykaa ✨

New makeup is always calling my name 💁‍♀️
@sheglam_official launched in India & I haven’t really tried their products before (as it was a part of shein) 
But their products are really affordable so I bought some to show you guys 🙌

Liquid contour in Golden Sun (which was extremely light for me) but the formula really melts into the skin & isn’t super pigmented so looks very natural on the skin 

Liquid Blush in Love Cake, this shade is such a pretty pink, & love how it looks dewy on the skin & again blends very easily (not sure how long it will last, since I have combination-oily skin)

Glam 101 Lipstick & Liner Duo in Soft Chai, this shade is of course not for me
But I do like it being a dual product so that’s great 

Lip liner in Neutral, is literally my lip shade, it’s a really pretty colour, & I do see myself reaching for this 

Flush Lip & Cheek Tint in Cherry is literally a dupe of the Benetint, & I do like to on my cheeks 

What do you guys think??

It’s available on @tirabeauty 
#nonsponsored 

#sheglam #newmakeup #makeupvideos

So impressed by these @typsybeauty 🩷 
The formula is very unique & looks so nice
I love that they experiment so much with their formulas & try to launch something different 

It looks very natural & is buildable 

You need the right brush to apply this , otherwise it can look patchy 
Not the most long lasting, so you will have to touch up

Lychee Lolly has to be my favourite shade 🩷 it’s like a peachy coral
